                    <head>No. 498.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Schuyler</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                    Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-03-17"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 17, 1875</date>.
                            (Received April 7.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 93.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose to you herewith,
                        marked 1, 2, and 3, the budget of the Russian Empire for 1875, the report of
                        the minister of finances thereon, and the report of the credit
                        establishments for 1873.</p>
                    <p>Omitting the items which balance on both sides of the budget, the receipts
                        for 1875 are estimated at 532,306,209 rubles, and the expenses at
                        529,050,426 rubles, leaving a surplus of 3,255,783 rubles.</p>
                    <p>The treasury receipts have been constantly increasing for the last few years,
                        since the improved administration of the finances under the present
